  "local_port": 52912,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I know if someone blocks me on Facebook messenger?",
  "response": "If someone blocks you on Facebook Messenger, there are a few signs that can indicate this has happened:\n\n1. **Messages Not Delivered**: When you send a message, you won't see the usual \"delivered\" or \"seen\" indicators beneath your message. It might show that the message is still \"sending\" or have no status at all.\n\n2. **No Profile Access**: You won't be able to see the person's profile, and their profile picture may appear as a default image or disappear entirely.\n\n3. **No Interaction**: You won't be able to start a new conversation with them. If you try to send a message, it may not go through, or you might not be able to find them in your contacts.\n\n4. **Call Restrictions**: You won't be able to make voice or video calls to the person who blocked you.\n\n5. **No Activity Status**: You won't be able to see if the person is active or was recently active on Messenger.\n\nKeep in mind that some of these signs can also occur if the person has deactivated their account or if there are technical issues with Messenger. If you suspect you've been blocked, the best way to confirm is to try contacting the person through another method or ask a mutual friend if they can still see the person's profile and communicate with them.",
